In[42]:
import pytesseract
from pytesseract import Output
from PIL import Image

def extract_words_boxes(image_path):
    image = Image.open(image_path)
    data = pytesseract.image_to_data(image, output_type=Output.DICT)

    words = []
    boxes = []

    width, height = image.size

    for i in range(len(data['text'])):
        if int(data['conf'][i]) > 0 and data['text'][i].strip() != "":
            word = data['text'][i]
            (x, y, w, h) = (data['left'][i], data['top'][i], data['width'][i], data['height'][i])

            # Normalize bounding boxes to 0-1000 scale
            box = [
                int(1000 * x / width),
                int(1000 * y / height),
                int(1000 * (x + w) / width),
                int(1000 * (y + h) / height)
            ]

            words.append(word)
            boxes.append(box)
    
    return words, boxes, image

Some weights of LayoutLMv3ForTokenClassification were not initialized from the model checkpoint at microsoft/layoutlmv3-base and are newly initialized: ['classifier.bias', 'classifier.weight']
You should probably TRAIN this model on a down-stream task to be able to use it for predictions and inference.

import pytesseract
from PIL import Image
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.patches import Rectangle

# Load image
image = Image.open("pdf_images/page_1.png").convert("RGB")

# Extract OCR data (words + boxes)
ocr_data = pytesseract.image_to_data(image, lang="eng", output_type=pytesseract.Output.DICT)

# Visualize words
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 16))
ax.imshow(image)

n_boxes = len(ocr_data['level'])
for i in range(n_boxes):
    (x, y, w, h) = (ocr_data['left'][i], ocr_data['top'][i], ocr_data['width'][i], ocr_data['height'][i])
    word = ocr_data['text'][i]
    if word.strip() != "":
        ax.add_patch(Rectangle((x, y), w, h, edgecolor='blue', facecolor='none', linewidth=1))
        ax.text(x, y - 5, word, fontsize=8, color='blue')

plt.axis("off")
plt.title("Words Detected via OCR")
plt.show()

# Get all x and y coords from all words
all_x = []
all_y = []
for box in boxes:
    x_coords = [point[0] for point in box]
    y_coords = [point[1] for point in box]
    all_x.extend(x_coords)
    all_y.extend(y_coords)

# Get main text area (in normalized coords)
x0, y0 = min(all_x), min(all_y)
x1, y1 = max(all_x), max(all_y)

# Scale to image size
x0_img = x0 * image.width / 1000
y0_img = y0 * image.height / 1000
w = (x1 - x0) * image.width / 1000
h = (y1 - y0) * image.height / 1000

# Draw main block
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 15))
ax.imshow(image)

# Draw all word boxes (optional)
for box in boxes:
    x_coords = [p[0] for p in box]
    y_coords = [p[1] for p in box]
    x0w, y0w = min(x_coords), min(y_coords)
    x1w, y1w = max(x_coords), max(y_coords)
    rect = Rectangle((x0w * image.width / 1000, y0w * image.height / 1000),
                     (x1w - x0w) * image.width / 1000,
                     (y1w - y0w) * image.height / 1000,
                     linewidth=0.5, edgecolor='blue', facecolor='none')
    ax.add_patch(rect)

# Draw main text area (big red rectangle)
main_block = Rectangle((x0_img, y0_img), w, h, linewidth=2, edgecolor='red', facecolor='none')
ax.add_patch(main_block)

plt.axis("off")
plt.title("Main Text Area in Red")
plt.show()

def compute_iou(boxA, boxB):
    # Get coordinates of intersection
    xA = max(boxA[0], boxB[0])
    yA = max(boxA[1], boxB[1])
    xB = min(boxA[2], boxB[2])
    yB = min(boxA[3], boxB[3])
    
    interArea = max(0, xB - xA) * max(0, yB - yA)
    
    boxAArea = (boxA[2] - boxA[0]) * (boxA[3] - boxA[1])
    boxBArea = (boxB[2] - boxB[0]) * (boxB[3] - boxB[1])
    
    iou = interArea / float(boxAArea + boxBArea - interArea)
    return iou

# Example usage
pred_box = [100, 150, 400, 500]  # predicted by model
gt_box = [110, 140, 390, 480]    # ground truth

iou = compute_iou(pred_box, gt_box)
print("IoU:", round(iou, 3))

IoU: 0.857
